17 oaths and affirmations administered, depositions and affidavits executed, and other notarial
18 acts performed by any commissioned officer in active service of the armed forces of the
19 United States.
20 (b) Any person who is a member of the armed forces of the United States on active duty
21 in any capacity may also utilize a remote, online notary public duly licensed in any state
22 of this country to notarize any forms or documents required by state or local agencies for
23 matters involving taxation, titling, and licensing of a motor vehicle. This provision shall
24 not apply to any documents involving the conveyance of real estate, wills, or trusts, or to
25 motor vehicles not intended for personal use by the service member or his or her family."
26 SECTION 2.
27 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
